  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best contributions of india to the world in all fields?",
  "response": "India has made significant contributions to the world across various fields, influencing global culture, science, technology, philosophy, and more. Here are some of the most notable contributions:\n\n### **Philosophy and Spirituality**\n1. **Yoga and Meditation**: Originating in ancient India, yoga and meditation have become global practices for physical, mental, and spiritual well-being.\n2. **Vedas, Upanishads, and Bhagavad Gita**: These texts are foundational to Hinduism and have influenced global philosophy, ethics, and spirituality.\n3. **Buddhism and Jainism**: Both religions, founded in India, emphasize non-violence, compassion, and self-discipline, influencing millions worldwide.\n\n### **Mathematics and Science**\n1. **Decimal System and Zero**: India introduced the decimal system and the concept of zero, revolutionizing mathematics and enabling modern computation.\n2. **Algebra and Trigonometry**: Indian mathematicians like Aryabhata and Brahmagupta made pioneering contributions to algebra and trigonometry.\n3. **Medicine (Ayurveda)**: Ayurveda, a holistic system of medicine, emphasizes natural healing and has influenced alternative medicine globally.\n\n### **Literature and Arts**\n1. **Epics and Literature**: The Mahabharata and Ramayana are among the world\u2019s longest and most influential epics, inspiring art, literature, and culture globally.\n2. **Classical Music and Dance**: Indian classical music (e.g., Hindustani, Carnatic) and dance forms (e.g., Bharatanatyam, Kathak) are celebrated worldwide.\n3. **Bollywood**: India\u2019s film industry is one of the largest in the world, producing culturally rich and diverse content.\n\n### **Culinary Contributions**\n1. **Indian Cuisine**: Dishes like curry, biryani, samosa, and naan have become staples in global cuisine.\n2. **Spices**: India\u2019s rich spice trade has influenced global culinary traditions and revolutionized food preservation.\n\n### **Social and Political Influence**\n1. **Non-Violence (Ahimsa)**: Mahatma Gandhi\u2019s philosophy of non-violence inspired global movements for civil rights and freedom.\n2. **Democracy**: As the world\u2019s largest democracy, India serves as a model for managing diversity and upholding democratic values.\n\n### **Technology and Innovation**\n1. **Information Technology**: India is a global hub for IT services, software development, and innovation, contributing significantly to the tech industry.\n2. **Space Exploration**: The Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO) has made affordable and innovative advancements in space technology, including the Mars Orbiter Mission.\n\n### **Architecture and Design**\n1. **Taj Mahal and Other Monuments**: India\u2019s architectural marvels, like the Taj Mahal, are celebrated as UNESCO World Heritage Sites.\n2. **Temple Architecture**: Intricate temple designs, such as those in Khajuraho and Hampi, showcase India\u2019s artistic and engineering prowess.\n\n### **Languages and Literature**\n1. **Sanskrit**: One of the oldest languages, Sanskrit has influenced many languages and provided a foundation for linguistic studies.\n2. **Multilingualism**: India\u2019s linguistic diversity has contributed to global studies in language preservation and translation.\n\n### **Cultural and Festivals**\n1. **Diwali, Holi, and Other Festivals**: Indian festivals are celebrated worldwide, promoting cultural exchange and unity.\n2. **Textiles and Handicrafts**: Indian textiles, such as silk, cotton, and embroidery techniques, are renowned globally.\n\n### **Global Leadership and Advocacy**\n1. **United Nations and Peacekeeping**: India is one of the largest contributors to UN peacekeeping missions, promoting global peace and security.\n2. **Environmental Initiatives**: India has been a leader in advocating for renewable energy and sustainability on the global stage.\n\nIndia\u2019s contributions continue to shape the world in diverse and meaningful ways, reflecting its rich heritage, innovation, and resilience.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
